<item>
            <title>[SPARK-20156] Java String toLowerCase &quot;Turkish locale bug&quot; causes Spark problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-20156</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the regional setting of the operation system is Turkish, the famous java locale problem occurs (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-5931&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-5931&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1493&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1493&lt;/a&gt;). &lt;br/&gt;
e.g : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;SERDEINFO&quot; lowers to &quot;serde&#305;nfo&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;uniquetable&quot; uppers to &quot;UN&#304;QUETABLE&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;work around : &lt;br/&gt;
add -Duser.country=US -Duser.language=en to the end of the line &lt;br/&gt;
SPARK_SUBMIT_OPTS=&quot;$SPARK_SUBMIT_OPTS -Dscala.usejavacp=true&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in spark-shell.sh&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubunutu 16.04&lt;br/&gt;
Using Scala version 2.11.8 (Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM, Java 1.8.0_121)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
